{"ID":270342, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"342\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs341.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs343.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 342<\/div>\n  <div class=\"topic \">&ldquo;THE KING FOLLETT DISCOURSE&rdquo;<\/div>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Being and Kind of Being God Is;<\/div>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Immortality of the Intelligence of Man<\/div>\n  <div class=\"topic \">By Joseph Smith the Prophet<\/div>\n  <p class=\"summary\">President Joseph Smith delivered the following discourse before about twenty thousand Saints at the April\n  conference of the Church, 1844, being the funeral sermon of Elder King Follett. Reported by Willard Richards, Wilford\n  Woodruff, Thomas Bullock and William Clayton. This discourse was first published in the <i>Times and Seasons<\/i> of August\n  15, 1844:<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Beloved Saints, I will call the attention of this congregation<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> while I address you on the subject\n  of the dead. The decease of our beloved brother,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> Elder King Follett, who was crushed in a well by\n  the falling of a tub of rock, has more immediately led me to that subject. I have been requested to\n  speak by his friends and relatives, but inasmuch as there are a great many in this congregation who\n  live in this city as well as elsewhere, who have lost friends, I feel disposed to speak on the subject\n  in general, and offer you my ideas, so far as I have ability, and so far as I shall be inspired by the\n  Holy Spirit<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> to dwell on this subject.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">I want your prayers and faith<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> that I may have the instruction of Almighty God<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> and the gift of\n  the Holy Ghost,<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> so that I may set forth things that are true<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> and which can be easily comprehended\n  by you, and that the testimony may carry conviction to your hearts<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> and minds of the truth<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> of what\n  I shall say. Pray that the Lord may strengthen my lungs, stay the winds,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> and let the prayers of the\n  Saints<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> to heaven appear, that they may enter into the ears of the Lord of Sabaoth,<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> for the effectual\n  prayers of the righteous avail much.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> There is strength here, and I verily believe that your prayers\n  will be heard.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Before I enter fully into the investigation of the subject which is lying before me, I wish to pave\n  the way and bring up the subject from the beginning, that you may understand it. I will make a few\n  preliminaries, in order that you may understand the subject when I come to it. I do not intend to\n  please your ears<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> with superfluity of words or oratory, or with much learning;<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> but I intend to edify\n  you with the simple truths from heaven.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106136\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106136)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106136)\">Ex. 12:3<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109856\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109856)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109856)\">Eph. 6:21<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112132\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112132)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112132)\">Alma 34:3<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116068\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116068)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116068)\">D&amp;C 126:1<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110541\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110541)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110541)\">2 Pet. 1:21<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113355\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113355)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113355)\">D&amp;C 20:26<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111159\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111159)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111159)\">2 Ne. 6:11<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115447\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115447)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115447)\">D&amp;C 107:22<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113801\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113801)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113801)\">D&amp;C 43:12<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110987\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110987)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110987)\">1 Ne. 13:37<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113356\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113356)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113356)\">D&amp;C 20:26<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115767\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115767)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115767)\">D&amp;C 121:26<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106929\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onc